                    <li>OCARINA_AegisciteMantlegearHediff</li>
                </hediffDefnames>
            </li>
        </comps>
    </ThingDef>

    <ThingDef ParentName="ApparelBase">
        <defName>OCARINA_Apparel_ArchotechMantlegear</defName>
        <tickerType>Normal</tickerType>
        <label>archotech mantlegear</label>
        <description>A set of fabric or leather body straps and an advanced chest piece. While not being as protective as something like an actual piece of armor, mantlegear acts like a soft-exosuit, so to speak, improving the wearer's general movement abilities. In this case, the archotech mantlegear is, as the name implies, created by an archotech. It is a supreme upgrade compared to even the aegiscite mantlegear, and should be cherished.\n\nWhile mantlegear is traditionally worn by the Va'ji, any xenotype is capable of wearing it.</description>
        <smeltable>false</smeltable>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/Apparel/ArchotechMantlegear/Naked</texPath>
            <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
        </graphicData>
        <thingCategories>
